{
  "text": "Until now, field measurements of biogenic methanol emissions have mainly been performed over different types of forest (e.g. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Grasslands cover one quarter of the earth's land surface [CITATION_5] . Apart from studies concerning the methanol emissions due to harvesting [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] only few long-term flux studies exist for grassland [CITATION_9] [CITATION_10] . These are based on chamber measurements characterised by a low time resolution.",
